# This file is used for SMTP authentication with external relays
# If using Gmail SMTP relay, the start.sh script will update this file automatically
# based on your environment variables (RELAY_HOST, RELAY_PORT, RELAY_USER, RELAY_PASSWORD)

# Format: [mail_server]:port username:password
# Example for Gmail: 
# [smtp.gmail.com]:587 yourusername@gmail.com:your-app-password

# IMPORTANT: 
# 1. After changing this file manually, run: postmap hash:/etc/postfix/sasl/sasl_passwd
# 2. Restart the mail-server container

# For Gmail, you MUST use an App Password if you have 2-Step Verification enabled
# Get an App Password at: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords

# For local mail only, this file can be empty 